13 nonperson felony if the amount involved is at least $5,000 but less than
14 $25,000; a severity level 8, nonperson felony if the amount involved is at
15 least $1,000 but less than $5,000; and a class C nonperson misdemeanor if
16 the amount involved is less than $1,000. Any combination of fraudulent
17 acts as defined in subsection (a) that occur in a period of six consecutive
18 months and that involve $25,000 or more shall have a presumptive
19 sentence of imprisonment regardless of its location on the sentencing grid
20 block.
21 (f) In addition to any other penalty, a person who violates this statute
22 shall be ordered to make restitution to the insurer or any other person or
23 entity for any financial loss sustained as a result of such violation. An
24 insurer shall not be required to provide coverage or pay any claim
25 involving a fraudulent insurance act.
26 (g) For the purposes of this section:
27 (1) "Amount involved" means the greater of: (A) The actual
28 pecuniary harm resulting from the fraudulent insurance act; (B) the
29 pecuniary harm that was intended to result from the fraudulent insurance
30 act; or (C) the intended pecuniary harm that would have been impossible
31 or unlikely to occur, such as in a government sting operation or a fraud in
32 which the claim for payment or other benefit pursuant to an insurance
33 policy exceeded the allowed value. The aggregate dollar amount of the
34 fraudulent claims submitted to the insurance company shall constitute
35 prima facie evidence of the amount of intended loss and is sufficient to
36 establish the aggregate amount involved in the fraudulent insurance act, if
37 not rebutted; and
38 (2) "pecuniary harm" means harm that is monetary or that otherwise
39 is readily measurable in money, and does not include emotional distress,
40 harm to reputation or other non-economic harm.
41 (h) This act shall apply to all insurance applications, ratings, claims
42 and other benefits made pursuant to any insurance policy or automobile
43 assigned claims plan.

